missionEventData.data1: Red 1 head to the jump point immediately. Red 2 and 3 are already enroute.
There's the Convoy. The defectors have assured us that the Corvettes lasers have been disabled.
Red 2 and 3 focus on the Orcim and the Esorp. I'll take out the Arreis.

Alliance intelligence reports that the crew of the Imperial Corvette Bixby wish to defect. The Corvette is currently escorting an Imperial convoy through the Dellalt system. X-Wings from Red Squadron led by Flight Officer Keyan Farlander will jump in to destroy the Imperial freighters before the transport Dagger boards to help the crew secure the vessel. Be on your guard for any Imperial interference.
This is the transport Dagger. Cover us while we dock with the Bixby.
This is the Dagger we've completed docking but are encountering resistance on board the vessel.
Hey lead! An Imperial Frigate is exiting Hyperspace.
The Frigate is launching Ties. We need to give the Dagger more time.
We've secured the ship! Keep those Ties engaged while the Bixby and the Dagger move to the jump point.
We've secured the Bixby. Red Lead to all ships, make your escape to the jump point!

missionEventData.data2: In the far reaches of the Outer Rim a rebellion is forming. A rebel cell led by the frigate Redemption and ace pilot Keyan Farlander have been striking back against the evil galactic empire. But the Emperor is at the height of his power, and even now he is marshalling his forces at the edge of the mid-rim. But help has come from the most unlikely of places. The captain of an imperial corvette has sent the rebel freedom fighters a secret message, he wishes to defect...

missionEventData.data3: Well done, by keeping the Tie Fighters at bay we were able to secure the Bixby. The captain himself asked me to express his thanks for the rescue. But don’t get comfortable, we have troubling news…

missionEventData.data1: This is Ars Opus to flight control. Requesting permission to depart.
Flight control to Ars Opus. Authorisation granted and good luck.
Fly to the waypoint to activate hyperspace
Use R to cycle all available targets and G to select the target in front
Press F to target the nearest hostile craft
Use left shoulder button to cycle all available targets and the X button to select the target in front
Press the Y button to target the nearest hostile craft
